<p><span><em>All Star Comics</em> #3</span> (Winter, 1940) featured the first appearance of the
			<a href="../teams/dc/JSA.php" target="_blank">Justice Society of America</a>, initially an anthology collection showcasing some of 
			National Periodicals premier characters outside of their respective titles.</p><br />

			<p>The Justice Society regularly featured golden-age mainstays such as the <a href="../heroes/dc/AtomI.php" target="_blank">Atom</a>, 
			<a href="../heroes/dc/DrFate.php" target="_blank">Dr. Fate</a>, the <a href="../heroes/dc/FlashI.php" target="_blank">Flash</a>, 
			<a href="../heroes/dc/GreenLanternI.php" target="_blank">Green Lantern</a>, <a href="../heroes/dc/HawkmanI.php" target="_blank">Hawkman</a>, 
			<a href="../heroes/dc/HourmanI.php" target="_blank">Hourman</a>, <a href="../heroes/dc/SandmanI.php" target="_blank">Sandman</a> and the 
			<a href="../heroes/dc/SpectreI.php" target="_blank">Spectre</a>.</p><br />